<p>You must <a href='/docs/v2/our-platform/tutorials/datasets/contributing-datasets#08-Create-Dataset-Listing'>create your dataset listing</a> before you update the documentation.</p>

<p>Make a pull request to the <a href='https://github.com/QuantConnect/Documentation'>Documentation repository</a> with the following changes to add your dataset to the documentation:</p>
<ol>
    <li>Update the <span class='page-section-name'>Asset Classes</span> and <span class='page-section-name'>Assets Available</span> sections of the <a href='/docs/v2/our-platform/user-guides/live-trading/brokerages'>brokerage user guides</a>.</li>
    <li>Update the <span class='page-section-name'>Sourcing</span> section of the <a href='/docs/v2/our-platform/user-guides/live-trading/data-feeds'>data feed user guides</a>.</li>
</ol>

<p>After we merge your dataset into production, we will update the <a href='https://www.quantconnect.com/docs/v2/our-platform/getting-started/quantconnect#04-Data-Library'>Data Library image</a> if this is your organization's first dataset contribution and we will update the <a href='https://www.quantconnect.com/docs/v2/our-platform/user-guides/datasets/categories'>Categories</a> documentation if your dataset falls under a new category.</p>
